did.abstract: This collection contains information on the Bernard Knox lectures, departmental correspondence, student information and exams, programs, and class syllabi. They range in date from 1963-1996.

prefercite.head: Preferred citation
prefercite.p: Classics Department records, Special Collections Research Center, The George Washington University.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: Series 1 is closed to research for 25 years from date of record creation.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection contains information on the Bernard Knox lectures, departmental correspondence, student information and exams, programs, and class syllabi. They range in date from 1963-1996.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into four series three department record series and Professor Bernard Knox lectures.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes information on the Bernard Knox lectures, departmental records, prizes, M.A. student information and exams. They range in date from 1963-1988.
This series has a paper container list in the reading room, please ask staff for assistance.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes correspondence, flyers, faculty lists, programs, schedules, and papers from the Classics department. They range in date from 1964-1996.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes information on seminars, correspondence, course syllabi, lectures, and exams. There is also course material written by faculty. The material ranges in date from 1967-2005.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains audio cassette recordings of Professor Bernard Knox lectures. These tapes were originally given to the Media Resources department at Gelman Library as a reserve. Media transferred these two the Classics Department when Dr. Knox was no longer teaching. Dr. John Ziolkowski gave them to the University Archives.
